  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As a user, I would like to have swipeable navigation, similar to WeChat. This makes things so much easier, so I don't have to reach for a specific button in the top left corner to go back to the previous page.\r\n\r\nIdea: On a chat page, You can swipe L>R to go back, and R>L to open the other person's profile, or if in a group open the group info page.\r\n\r\n## Examples:\r\n\r\nHow WeChat does it:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65834069/148661245-4aeac22f-bb54-477b-af72-8098a79d0365.mp4\r\n\r\nHow GETTR does it:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65834069/148661429-0aa29906-5282-48c1-95ef-3eaa7bea8d4f.mp4\r\n",
